thread.title: Asian Stocks Weaken as Investors Look to State of the Union

author: Kenan Machado
title: Asian Stocks Weaken as Investors Look to State of the Union
text:
U.S. stocks rebound Boeing rallies after earnings Treasury yields rise ahead of Fed statement U.S. stocks rebounded Wednesday following their worst two-day stretch in months, lifted by the latest round of corporate earnings.
Some investors said the drops earlier in the week were healthy following a rapid run-up in stocks that pushed major indexes to fresh records. They added that a positive earnings and economic backdrop remains intact following recent tax changes.
